  "prompt": "Is Facebook banned in Cuba?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, Facebook is not officially banned in Cuba. However, access to the platform and other social media sites can be intermittent due to Cuba's limited internet infrastructure and government restrictions on internet access. The Cuban government has been known to temporarily block or restrict access to certain websites and platforms during periods of political unrest or protests.\n\nWhile Facebook remains accessible to many Cubans, the experience of using it can vary widely depending on the availability of internet services and the specific policies in place at any given time. For the most current and accurate information, it's best to consult recent reports or updates from reliable sources.",
